liam.collections

Class Bag<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • liam.collections.Bag<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of items to be added.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>

    public class Bag<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<T>
    This collection class is like a bag of items. This means that values stored in this class will be fetched randomly (mirroring the nature of an actual bag).
    Author:
    Liam
